{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandate public transport operators prohibit balaclavas except religious/medical",
        "additional_details": "Crime on public transport is rising, often facilitated by offenders wearing balaclavas to evade CCTV and intimidate passengers.\r\n\r\n\u200bSafety: Identifying offenders is currently impossible, rendering CCTV useless. \u200bContext: There is no reasonable need for thermal face coverings inside heated vehicles, distinguishing them from religious garments or medical masks. \u200bEnforcement: Police need clear powers to demand removal without a Section 60 order, making it a Condition of Carriage does this.",
        "background": "Require public transport operators (including TfL and National Rail) to amend Byelaws and Conditions of Carriage to prohibit the wearing of balaclavas and identity-concealing masks (excluding those worn for legitimate religious or medical reasons).\u200b",
